&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cerebral takes a holistic and comprehensive approach when providing care for our patients. Our telemedicine therapists collaborate with prescribers as needed, to support clients during their mental health journey. This therapist role provides direct care for a panel of clients and allows for flexibility when client sessions can be scheduled. You can see clients during traditional business hours, evenings, or on weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current state license requirements include: Alabama, Arkansas, California, Colorado, Florida, Georgia, Iowa, Maryland, Massachusetts, Missouri, Nebraska, North Carolina, New Jersey, New York, Nevada, Ohio, South Dakota, Virginia, Washington, and West Virginia.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If licensed in Iowa, Nebraska, or South Dakota, you must also reside in that designated state due to current payer requirements.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These positions are 1099 independent contractor opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
